snippet: Mr. van Zweden, likely a candidate for the orchestra’s music directorship, led an inventive performance of Beethoven, Mozart and Britten.
abstract: Zachary Woolfe reviews New York Philharmonic concert with guest conductor Jaap van Zweden, who may be candidate for music director, at David Geffen Hall.
lead_paragraph: Mr. van Zweden, likely a candidate for the orchestra’s music directorship, led an inventive performance of Beethoven, Mozart and Britten.

headline.print_headline: A Rare Mix of Precision and Seduction
headline.main: Review: Jaap van Zweden, Precise at the New York Philharmonic
